        <p class="metadata">Posted by Matthew Weier O'Phinney (matthew) on 2007-04-04T13:08:55.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>There's been a fair amount of discussion of this topic on the fw-mvc list, and I'm not sure it's appropriate to make this change. The idea of _redirect() is for general redirection, and not necessarily redirection within the site itself.</p>

<p>Probably a better idea is to create an additional method, createUrl(), that could be used by _forward() and also used to generate a URL to pass to _redirect(); an option in the $options array passed to _redirect() could be used to indicate that the URL should be generated via createUrl().</p>

<p>I will consider the issue, but cannot guarantee it will be ready prior to the 1.0.0 release.</p>

        </div>
